            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190707-62-person611">
                  JOHN 
                  NEWMAN
               <interp inst="t18190707-62-person611" type="surname" value="NEWMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190707-62-person611" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190707-62-person611" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18190707-62-viclabel330" type="occupation">dyer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190707-62-victim610 t18190707-62-viclabel330"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18190707-62-crimeloc331">Artillery-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190707-62-crimeloc331" type="placeName" value="Artillery-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190707-62-crimeloc331" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190707-62-off328 t18190707-62-crimeloc331"></join>. On the 25th of May, while I was out, I lost the moreen from my shop. In consequence of what I heard, I met the prisoner next day, and asked him who authorized him to fetch the furniture away? he said he was half drunk. I asked him why he did not bring it back? he said it was in some dying liquor, and I could not have until it was done - he kept promising, but never brought it, and I had him apprehended. He said he had lost it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Had you not asked me to dye it - A. I asked him what he would charge.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190707-62-person612">
                  ELIZABETH 
                  SPEARS
               <interp inst="t18190707-62-person612" type="surname" value="SPEARS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190707-62-person612" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190707-62-person612" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Newman, The prisoner came and asked if my master was at home? I said No - I did not know him before. He said he came for the curtains (pointing to them). I asked him what colour they were to be dyed? he said</p>
               <p>"crimson." I told<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181907070022"></xptr>him he must stop until my master came in. I went into the parlour to the child, he went out with the moreen. - He told me his name.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. He told me to fetch them. I was robbed of them, and offered to pay him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190707-62-person613">
                  JOHN 
                  NEWMAN
               <interp inst="t18190707-62-person613" type="surname" value="NEWMAN"></interp>
